BRIEFING:
A FRONT TO THE NORTH AND A SURFACE RIDGE TO THE SOUTH OF THE HAWAIIAN ISLANDS WILL MAINTAIN LIGHT TO MODERATE SOUTHERLY WINDS. THESE SOUTHERLY WINDS ARE EXPECTED THROUGH AT LEAST TOMORROW. DRY AND STABLE CONDS WITH ISOL SHRA AND LOW CIGS POSSIBLE. BRIEF MVFR CONDS CAN BE EXPECTED IN SHRA, OTHERWISE VFR PREVAILS.
HAZY CONDS SHOULD CONTINUE THROUGH AT LEAST TOMORROW DUE TO KILAUEA VOLCANIC ACTIVITY AND SOUTHERLY WINDS. THIS COULD LEAD TO POCKETS OF REDUCED VSBYS.
NO AIRMETS IN EFFECT.
